          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two self-supporting 24Mg metallic foils were used as",
                "a targets.",
                "A 12 mg/cm2 target was used to give larger counting",
                "rates when energy resolution was not a limiting factor;",
                "otherwise a 6 mg/cm2 target was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two different detection systems were used to",
                "measure the positions of the proton groups in the",
                "focal plane. The first system consisted of two",
                "wedge-shaped scintillators with a dE/dx counters",
                "placed in front of each wedge. These counters consisted",
                "of 0.5 mm thick NE 102A plastic scintillator mounted",
                "on perspex light guides.",
                "In the second an acoustic spark chamber was used.",
                "The chamber was triggered using the  coincidence pulse",
                "obtained from the two dE/dx counters placed behind the",
                "spark chamber. These counters consisted of 0.6 mm thick",
                "NE 102A plastic scintillator mounted on perspex light",
                "guides."
              ]
            }
          ],
